GENERAL WARRANTY DEED
VOL 539 PAGE 794
15637

RALPH E. CARMACK and FRANCES H. CARMACK, Husband and Wife
(1), of Tuscarawas County, Ohio

for valuable consideration paid, grant(s), with general warranty covenants, to EUGENE E. BARKLEY, whose tax-mailing address is
500 Johnson Avenue, Dennison, Ohio 44621

the following REAL PROPERTY: Situated in the County of Tuscarawas in the State of Ohio and in the Township of Union:

Being a part of the Southeast Quarter of Section No. Twenty-five (25), Township Fourteen (14), Range Seven (7), and being a part of a 38.88 acre tract as conveyed to Ralph E. and Frances H. Carmack by a deed as recorded in Volume 280, Page 20 of the Tuscarawas County Deed Records, and being more fully described as follows:

Beginning at an iron pin at the Northwest corner of the Southeast Quarter of Section No. Twenty-five (25); thence with the North line of said Southeast Quarter, South 86°-23' East, 315.94 feet to a point in the center of a creek; thence with the center of said creek the following two (2) courses and distances: South 13°-59' East, 562.4 feet and South 8°-32' East, 326.7 feet to a point in the center of County Road No. 37; thence with the center of County Road No. 37, South 77°-38' West, 550.0 feet to an iron pin on the West line of said Southeast Quarter; thence North 2°-07' East, 1009.20 feet to the place of beginning, containing 9.480 acres, more or less, but subject to all legal highways.

The above description prepared by Frank E. Bair, P.S. Reg. Surveyor #5918.

Taxes shall be prorated as of the date of closing.

Prior Instrument Reference: Vol. 280 Page 20 of the Deed Records of Tuscarawas County, Ohio.

Witness their hand(s) this 20 day of June, 1978.

Signed and acknowledged in the presence of:
[signatures of witnesses and grantors]

State of Ohio
County of Tuscarawas ss.

BE IT REMEMBERED, That on this 20 day of June, 1978, before me, the subscriber, a Notary Public in and for said county, personally came, RALPH E. CARMACK and FRANCES H. CARMACK, Husband and wife the Grantor(s) in the foregoing Deed, and acknowledged the signing thereof to be their voluntary act and deed.

IN TESTIMONY WHEREOF, I have hereunto subscribed my name and affixed my seal on this day and year aforesaid.
[Notary signature and seal]
TRANSFERRED
This instrument prepared by William A. Kyler, Attorney

RECEIVED FOR RECORD
JUN 23 1978
15637
